Phillips v. McCall & McClure. Appeal from Madison Circuit ■ Court — Saturday, January 28. V. Waimoright for the appellant — John Leona/rcL for the appellee.

• Action to recover for work and labor performed. The case turned entirely upon its facts, and the judgment of the court below, in favor of plaintiff, was affirmed as being sustained by the evidence.

Cole, J.,' delivering the opinion. ■
